translation.text: Inner West & Leppington Line - Good service

Services to/from Leppington will now terminate at/commence from Homebush instead of Strathfield due to overhead wiring repairs between Homebush and Flemington. Western Line services to/from Penrith/Emu Plains will make an additional stop at Flemington in both directions. Please continue to allow additional travel time as you may have to change trains to complete your journey and may experience longer journey times.  Repair crews are onsite and at this stage, services are forecast to return to normal from approximately 20:00.

Trains have been suspended between Dapto and Kiama due to signal equipment repairs at Minnamurra. A limited replacement bus service has been arranged between Dapto and Kiama. Major delays are being experienced in the affected area.
With extreme heat conditions forecast today, please stay hydrated. If you feel unwell, don't risk boarding a train. Station staff can assist you.

Christmas at Rosehill Gardens - Rosehill Gardens, Rosehill
13:00 to 18:30
- Race goers are encouraged to make use of the parking on-site at Rosehill Gardens and drive with their groups or use taxis and rideshare.
- The best station for connections to Rosehill Gardens is Parramatta where you can change for buses to get to and from the racecourse.
- Catch Route 535 buses from Valentine Ave on the southern side of Parramatta Interchange to the Camellia/Rosehill stop on Hassall St.

Spring Racing Race Day - Kembla Grange Racecourse
12:00 to 18:00
- All South Coast services will make an additional stop at Kembla Grange station between 11:00 and 19:00.

Tri Nations Rugby: Argentina v New Zealand - McDonald Jones Stadium, Broadmeadow
19:45 to 20:30
- Fans are encouraged to drive to the game and use the available parking at the stadium and surrounding streets.
- The closest station to the Stadium is Broadmeadow on the Central Coast & Newcastle Line. From the station, the stadium is approximately a 15-20 minute walk away (1.5km).
- Free shuttle buses will run on different routes with return services running after the game.  

Greatest Southern Nights: Ocean Alley Concert - Qudos Bank Arena, Sydney Olympic Park
21:30 to 22:45
- Attendees are urged to drive with their group and use the available car parks at Sydney Olympic Park.
- Trains from Lidcomnbe to Olympic Park run every 10 minutes until late.

For further information please visit https://transportnsw.info/events/2020/11

There are changes happening at Central Station due to Sydney Metro construction works. Access to certain areas of the station and platforms may be limited, which means using different stairs, escalators and lifts. Please follow the signs and staff directions. If you need assistance, see station staff. For detailed information please visit https://transportnsw.info/alerts/details#/6049959

Access to the station from Como Parade will be temporarily unavailable from Monday 30 November whilst station updgrade work is being completed. During this time, please enter and exit the station via Railway Road entrance.

New Metro Platforms are being constructed on platforms 1 & 2 at Sydenham Station.
T3 Bankstown Line services to the City operate from platform 3 & T3 Bankstown Line services to Lidcombe and Liverpool operate from platform 4.
Platform 4, 5 & 6 upgrade works - A new Metro concourse is also being constructed at the Northern end of the station. While the concourse is being installed, please board and alight from the first 5 carriages of the train on platforms 4 & 6 and the last 6 carriages of the train on platform 5.
If you need help, please see staff at the station. For more information on these upgrades, please see sydneymetro.info

Monday 30 November to Thursday 03 December - Nightly from 8pm until 4:30am - The George St entrance/exit to Wynyard Station, Transit Hall and Hunter Tunnel will all be closed for station upgrade works. Access to/from the station is still available via Carrington St, York St & Barangaroo. Please follow the signs and staff directions. If you need assistance, see station staff or call 9224 2959.
